noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 we can see that for 
\begin_inset Formula $K=1$
\end_inset

 definitely shouldn't occur synchronization (identified by 
\begin_inset Formula $r=1$
\end_inset

), and for 
\begin_inset Formula $K=2$
\end_inset

 it should, and these stabilization 
\begin_inset Formula $r$
\end_inset

 values seem to be roughly the same as those obtained in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:rk1"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Uniform distribution of the natural frequencies
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We now turn to the case where we have a uniform distribution of the natural
 frequencies between 
\begin_inset Formula $-\frac{1}{2}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{1}{2}$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
g(\omega)=\left\{ \begin{array}{ll}
1, & |\omega|\leq\frac{1}{2}\\
0, & |\omega|>\frac{1}{2}
\end{array}\right.
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

